tachyon.client

Class TachyonFS

  • java.lang.Object
    • tachyon.client.TachyonFS

  • public class TachyonFS
extends Object
    Client API to use Tachyon as a file system. This API is not compatible with HDFS file system API; while AbstractTFS provides another API that exposes Tachyon as HDFS file system. Under the hood, this class maintains a MasterClient to talk to the master server and WorkerClients to interact with different Tachyon workers.

      • setPinned

        public void setPinned(int fid,
             boolean pinned)
               throws IOException
        Sets the "pinned" flag for the given file. Pinned files are never evicted by Tachyon until they are unpinned. Calling setPinned() on a folder will recursively set the "pinned" flag on all of that folder's children. This may be an expensive operation for folders with many files/subfolders.
        Throws:
        IOException
